{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":2000,"text":"Martin Luther King"},{"time":4000,"text":"did not say,"},{"time":6000,"text":"\"I have a nightmare,\""},{"time":8000,"text":"when he inspired the civil rights movements."},{"time":11000,"text":"He said, \"I have a dream.\""},{"time":14000,"text":"And I have a dream."},{"time":16000,"text":"I have a dream that we can stop thinking"},{"time":18000,"text":"that the future will be a nightmare,"},{"time":21000,"text":"and this is going to be a challenge,"},{"time":23000,"text":"because, if you think"},{"time":25000,"text":"of every major blockbusting film of recent times,"},{"time":29000,"text":"nearly all of its visions for humanity"},{"time":32000,"text":"are apocalyptic."},{"time":34000,"text":"I think this film"},{"time":36000,"text":"is one of the hardest watches of modern times, \"The Road.\""},{"time":39000,"text":"It's a beautiful piece of filmmaking,"},{"time":41000,"text":"but everything is desolate,"},{"time":43000,"text":"everything is dead."},{"time":46000,"text":"And just a father and son"},{"time":48000,"text":"trying to survive, walking along the road."},{"time":51000,"text":"And I think the environmental movement"},{"time":53000,"text":"of which I am a part of"},{"time":55000,"text":"has been complicit"},{"time":57000,"text":"in creating this vision of the future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":59000,"text":"For too long,"},{"time":61000,"text":"we have peddled a nightmarish vision"},{"time":63000,"text":"of what's going to happen."},{"time":65000,"text":"We have focused on the worst-case scenario."},{"time":68000,"text":"We have focused on the problems."},{"time":70000,"text":"And we have not thought enough"},{"time":72000,"text":"about the solutions."},{"time":74000,"text":"We've used fear, if you like,"},{"time":76000,"text":"to grab people's attention."},{"time":79000,"text":"And any psychologist will tell you"},{"time":82000,"text":"that fear in the organism"},{"time":84000,"text":"is linked to flight mechanism."},{"time":86000,"text":"It's part of the fight and flight mechanism,"},{"time":89000,"text":"that when an animal is frightened --"},{"time":91000,"text":"think of a deer."},{"time":93000,"text":"A deer freezes very, very still,"},{"time":96000,"text":"poised to run away."},{"time":98000,"text":"And I think that's what we're doing"},{"time":100000,"text":"when we're asking people to engage with our agenda"},{"time":103000,"text":"around environmental degradation and climate change."},{"time":106000,"text":"People are freezing and running away"},{"time":109000,"text":"because we're using fear."},{"time":111000,"text":"And I think the environmental movement has to grow up"},{"time":114000,"text":"and start to think about"},{"time":116000,"text":"what progress is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":118000,"text":"What would it be like to be improving the human lot?"},{"time":121000,"text":"And one of the problems that we face, I think,"},{"time":123000,"text":"is that the only people that have cornered the market"},{"time":126000,"text":"in terms of progress"},{"time":128000,"text":"is a financial definition of what progress is,"},{"time":131000,"text":"an economic definition of what progress is --"},{"time":134000,"text":"that somehow,"},{"time":136000,"text":"if we get the right numbers to go up,"},{"time":138000,"text":"we're going to be better off,"},{"time":141000,"text":"whether that's on the stock market,"},{"time":143000,"text":"whether that's with GDP"},{"time":145000,"text":"and economic growth,"},{"time":147000,"text":"that somehow life is going to get better."},{"time":149000,"text":"This is somehow appealing to human greed"},{"time":152000,"text":"instead of fear --"},{"time":154000,"text":"that more is better."},{"time":156000,"text":"Come on. In the Western world, we have enough."},{"time":159000,"text":"Maybe some parts of the world don't, but we have enough."},{"time":162000,"text":"And we've know for a long time that this is not a good measure"},{"time":165000,"text":"of the welfare of nations."},{"time":167000,"text":"In fact, the architect of our national accounting system,"},{"time":170000,"text":"Simon Kuznets, in the 1930s,"},{"time":173000,"text":"said that, \"A nation's welfare"},{"time":175000,"text":"can scarcely be inferred from their national income.\""},{"time":178000,"text":"But we've created a national accounting system"},{"time":180000,"text":"which is firmly based on production"},{"time":182000,"text":"and producing stuff."},{"time":184000,"text":"And indeed, this is probably historical, and it had its time."},{"time":187000,"text":"In the second World War, we needed to produce a lot of stuff."},{"time":190000,"text":"And indeed, we were so successful at producing certain types of stuff"},{"time":193000,"text":"that we destroyed a lot of Europe, and we had to rebuild it afterwards."},{"time":196000,"text":"And so our national accounting system"},{"time":198000,"text":"became fixated on what we can produce."}]},{"cues":[{"time":201000,"text":"But as early as 1968,"},{"time":204000,"text":"this visionary man, Robert Kennedy,"},{"time":207000,"text":"at the start of his ill-fated presidential campaign,"},{"time":210000,"text":"gave the most eloquent deconstruction"},{"time":213000,"text":"of gross national product"},{"time":215000,"text":"that ever has been."},{"time":217000,"text":"And he finished his talk with the phrase,"},{"time":220000,"text":"that, \"The gross national product"},{"time":222000,"text":"measures everything except that"},{"time":225000,"text":"which makes life worthwhile.\""},{"time":227000,"text":"How crazy is that? That our measure of progress,"},{"time":230000,"text":"our dominant measure of progress in society,"},{"time":233000,"text":"is measuring everything"},{"time":235000,"text":"except that which makes life worthwhile?"},{"time":238000,"text":"I believe, if Kennedy was alive today,"},{"time":241000,"text":"he would be asking statisticians such as myself"},{"time":244000,"text":"to go out and find out"},{"time":246000,"text":"what makes life worthwhile."},{"time":248000,"text":"He'd be asking us to redesign"},{"time":250000,"text":"our national accounting system"},{"time":252000,"text":"to be based upon"},{"time":254000,"text":"such important things as social justice,"},{"time":257000,"text":"sustainability"},{"time":259000,"text":"and people's well-being."}]},{"cues":[{"time":261000,"text":"And actually, social scientists have already gone out"},{"time":263000,"text":"and asked these questions around the world."},{"time":265000,"text":"This is from a global survey."},{"time":267000,"text":"It's asking people, what do they want."},{"time":270000,"text":"And unsurprisingly, people all around the world"},{"time":273000,"text":"say that what they want"},{"time":275000,"text":"is happiness, for themselves,"},{"time":277000,"text":"for their families, their children,"},{"time":279000,"text":"their communities."},{"time":281000,"text":"Okay, they think money is slightly important."},{"time":283000,"text":"It's there, but it's not nearly as important as happiness,"},{"time":286000,"text":"and it's not nearly as important as love."},{"time":289000,"text":"We all need to love and be loved in life."},{"time":292000,"text":"It's not nearly as important as health."},{"time":294000,"text":"We want to be healthy and live a full life."},{"time":297000,"text":"These seem to be natural human aspirations."},{"time":300000,"text":"Why are statisticians not measuring these?"},{"time":303000,"text":"Why are we not thinking of the progress of nations in these terms,"},{"time":306000,"text":"instead of just how much stuff we have?"},{"time":309000,"text":"And really, this is what I've done with my adult life --"},{"time":312000,"text":"is think about how do we measure happiness,"},{"time":314000,"text":"how do we measure well-being,"},{"time":316000,"text":"how can we do that within environmental limits."}]},{"cues":[{"time":318000,"text":"And we created, at the organization that I work for,"},{"time":320000,"text":"the New Economics Foundation,"},{"time":322000,"text":"something we call the Happy Planet Index,"},{"time":325000,"text":"because we think people should be happy and the planet should be happy."},{"time":328000,"text":"Why don't we create a measure of progress that shows that?"},{"time":331000,"text":"And what we do,"},{"time":333000,"text":"is we say that the ultimate outcome of a nation"},{"time":335000,"text":"is how successful is it"},{"time":337000,"text":"at creating happy and healthy lives for its citizens."},{"time":340000,"text":"That should be the goal"},{"time":342000,"text":"of every nation on the planet."},{"time":344000,"text":"But we have to remember"},{"time":346000,"text":"that there's a fundamental input to that,"},{"time":349000,"text":"and that is how many of the planet's resources we use."},{"time":352000,"text":"We all have one planet. We all have to share it."},{"time":355000,"text":"It is the ultimate scarce resource,"},{"time":358000,"text":"the one planet that we share."},{"time":361000,"text":"And economics is very interested in scarcity."},{"time":364000,"text":"When it has a scarce resource"},{"time":366000,"text":"that it wants to turn into"},{"time":368000,"text":"a desirable outcome,"},{"time":370000,"text":"it thinks in terms of efficiency."},{"time":373000,"text":"It thinks in terms of how much bang do we get for our buck."},{"time":376000,"text":"And this is a measure of how much well-being"},{"time":378000,"text":"we get for our planetary resource use."},{"time":381000,"text":"It is an efficiency measure."},{"time":383000,"text":"And probably the easiest way to show you that,"},{"time":386000,"text":"is to show you this graph."}]},{"cues":[{"time":388000,"text":"Running horizontally along the graph,"},{"time":391000,"text":"is \"ecological footprint,\""},{"time":393000,"text":"which is a measure of how much resources we use"},{"time":396000,"text":"and how much pressure we put on the planet."},{"time":398000,"text":"More is bad."},{"time":400000,"text":"Running vertically upwards,"},{"time":402000,"text":"is a measure called \"happy life years.\""},{"time":404000,"text":"It's about the well-being of nations."},{"time":406000,"text":"It's like a happiness adjusted life-expectancy."},{"time":409000,"text":"It's like quality and quantity of life in nations."},{"time":412000,"text":"And the yellow dot there you see, is the global average."},{"time":415000,"text":"Now, there's a huge array of nations"},{"time":417000,"text":"around that global average."},{"time":419000,"text":"To the top right of the graph,"},{"time":422000,"text":"are countries which are doing reasonably well and producing well-being,"},{"time":425000,"text":"but they're using a lot of planet to get there."},{"time":427000,"text":"They are the U.S.A.,"},{"time":429000,"text":"other Western countries going across in those triangles"},{"time":432000,"text":"and a few Gulf states in there actually."},{"time":434000,"text":"Conversely, at the bottom left of the graph,"},{"time":437000,"text":"are countries that are not producing much well-being --"},{"time":440000,"text":"typically, sub-Saharan Africa."},{"time":443000,"text":"In Hobbesian terms,"},{"time":445000,"text":"life is short and brutish there."},{"time":447000,"text":"The average life expectancy in many of these countries"},{"time":450000,"text":"is only 40 years."},{"time":453000,"text":"Malaria, HIV/AIDS"},{"time":455000,"text":"are killing a lot of people"},{"time":457000,"text":"in these regions of the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":459000,"text":"But now for the good news!"},{"time":461000,"text":"There are some countries up there, yellow triangles,"},{"time":463000,"text":"that are doing better than global average,"},{"time":465000,"text":"that are heading up towards the top left of the graph."},{"time":467000,"text":"This is an aspirational graph."},{"time":469000,"text":"We want to be top left, where good lives don't cost the earth."},{"time":472000,"text":"They're Latin American."},{"time":474000,"text":"The country on its own up at the top"},{"time":476000,"text":"is a place I haven't been to."},{"time":478000,"text":"Maybe some of you have."},{"time":480000,"text":"Costa Rica."},{"time":484000,"text":"Costa Rica --"},{"time":486000,"text":"average life expectancy is 78-and-a-half years."},{"time":489000,"text":"That is longer than in the USA."},{"time":493000,"text":"They are, according to the latest Gallup world poll,"},{"time":496000,"text":"the happiest nation on the planet --"},{"time":499000,"text":"than anybody; more than Switzerland and Denmark."},{"time":502000,"text":"They are the happiest place."},{"time":504000,"text":"They are doing that"},{"time":506000,"text":"on a quarter of the resources"},{"time":508000,"text":"that are used typically in [the] Western world --"},{"time":511000,"text":"a quarter of the resources."}]},{"cues":[{"time":514000,"text":"What's going on there?"},{"time":517000,"text":"What's happening in Costa Rica?"},{"time":519000,"text":"We can look at some of the data."},{"time":521000,"text":"99 percent of their electricity comes from renewable resources."},{"time":524000,"text":"Their government is one of the first to commit"},{"time":526000,"text":"to be carbon neutral by 2021."},{"time":529000,"text":"They abolished the army"},{"time":532000,"text":"in 1949 --"},{"time":534000,"text":"1949."},{"time":536000,"text":"And they invested in social programs --"},{"time":538000,"text":"health and education."},{"time":540000,"text":"They have one of the highest literacy rates in Latin America"},{"time":543000,"text":"and in the world."},{"time":545000,"text":"And they have that Latin vibe, don't they."},{"time":547000,"text":"They have the social connectedness."},{"time":549000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":551000,"text":"The challenge is, that possibly -- and the thing we might have to think about --"},{"time":554000,"text":"is that the future"},{"time":556000,"text":"might not be North American,"},{"time":558000,"text":"might not be Western European."},{"time":560000,"text":"It might be Latin American."},{"time":563000,"text":"And the challenge, really,"},{"time":565000,"text":"is to pull the global average up here."},{"time":568000,"text":"That's what we need to do."},{"time":570000,"text":"And if we're going to do that,"},{"time":572000,"text":"we need to pull countries from the bottom,"},{"time":575000,"text":"and we need to pull countries from the right of the graph."},{"time":578000,"text":"And then we're starting to create a happy planet."},{"time":581000,"text":"That's one way of looking at it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":583000,"text":"Another way of looking at it is looking at time trends."},{"time":585000,"text":"We don't have good data going back for every country in the world,"},{"time":588000,"text":"but for some of the richest countries, the OECD group, we do."},{"time":591000,"text":"And this is the trend in well-being over that time,"},{"time":594000,"text":"a small increase,"},{"time":596000,"text":"but this is the trend in ecological footprint."},{"time":598000,"text":"And so in strict happy-planet methodology,"},{"time":601000,"text":"we've become less efficient"},{"time":603000,"text":"at turning our ultimate scarce resource"},{"time":605000,"text":"into the outcome we want to."},{"time":608000,"text":"And the point really is, is that I think,"},{"time":611000,"text":"probably everybody in this room"},{"time":613000,"text":"would like society to get to 2050"},{"time":615000,"text":"without an apocalyptic"},{"time":618000,"text":"something happening."},{"time":620000,"text":"It's actually not very long away."},{"time":622000,"text":"It's half a human lifetime away."},{"time":624000,"text":"A child entering school today"},{"time":626000,"text":"will be my age in 2050."},{"time":628000,"text":"This is not the very distant future."},{"time":631000,"text":"This is what the U.K. government target"},{"time":634000,"text":"on carbon and greenhouse emissions looks like."},{"time":638000,"text":"And I put it to you, that is not business as usual."},{"time":641000,"text":"That is changing our business."},{"time":643000,"text":"That is changing the way we create our organizations,"},{"time":646000,"text":"we do our government policy and we live our lives."},{"time":649000,"text":"And the point is,"},{"time":651000,"text":"we need to carry on increasing well-being."},{"time":653000,"text":"No one can go to the polls"},{"time":655000,"text":"and say that quality of life is going to reduce."},{"time":658000,"text":"None of us, I think,"},{"time":660000,"text":"want human progress to stop."},{"time":662000,"text":"I think we want it to carry on."},{"time":664000,"text":"I think we want the lot of humanity to keep on increasing."},{"time":666000,"text":"And I think this is where climate change skeptics and deniers come in."},{"time":669000,"text":"I think this is what they want. They want quality of life to keep increasing."},{"time":672000,"text":"They want to hold on to what they've got."},{"time":675000,"text":"And if we're going to engage them,"},{"time":677000,"text":"I think that's what we've got to do."},{"time":679000,"text":"And that means we have to really increase efficiency even more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":682000,"text":"Now that's all very easy to draw graphs and things like that,"},{"time":685000,"text":"but the point is we need to turn those curves."},{"time":688000,"text":"And this is where I think we can take a leaf"},{"time":690000,"text":"out of systems theory, systems engineers,"},{"time":693000,"text":"where they create feedback loops,"},{"time":695000,"text":"put the right information at the right point of time."},{"time":698000,"text":"Human beings are very motivated by the \"now.\""},{"time":701000,"text":"You put a smart meter in your home,"},{"time":703000,"text":"and you see how much electricity you're using right now,"},{"time":705000,"text":"how much it's costing you,"},{"time":707000,"text":"your kids go around and turn the lights off pretty quickly."},{"time":710000,"text":"What would that look like for society?"},{"time":713000,"text":"Why is it, on the radio news every evening,"},{"time":715000,"text":"I hear the FTSE 100, the Dow Jones, the dollar pound ratio --"},{"time":718000,"text":"I don't even know which way the dollar pound ratio should go to be good news."},{"time":721000,"text":"And why do I hear that?"},{"time":723000,"text":"Why don't I hear how much energy Britain used yesterday,"},{"time":726000,"text":"or American used yesterday?"},{"time":728000,"text":"Did we meet our three percent annual target"},{"time":730000,"text":"on reducing carbon emissions?"},{"time":732000,"text":"That's how you create a collective goal."},{"time":734000,"text":"You put it out there into the media and start thinking about it."},{"time":737000,"text":"And we need positive feedback loops"},{"time":740000,"text":"for increasing well-being"},{"time":742000,"text":"At a government level, they might create national accounts of well-being."},{"time":745000,"text":"At a business level, you might look at the well-being of your employees,"},{"time":748000,"text":"which we know is really linked to creativity,"},{"time":750000,"text":"which is linked to innovation,"},{"time":752000,"text":"and we're going to need a lot of innovation to deal with those environmental issues."},{"time":755000,"text":"At a personal level, we need these nudges too."},{"time":759000,"text":"Maybe we don't quite need the data, but we need reminders."},{"time":762000,"text":"In the U.K., we have a strong public health message"},{"time":765000,"text":"on five fruit and vegetables a day"},{"time":767000,"text":"and how much exercise we should do -- never my best thing."},{"time":770000,"text":"What are these for happiness?"},{"time":773000,"text":"What are the five things that you should do every day"},{"time":775000,"text":"to be happier?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":777000,"text":"We did a project for the Government Office of Science a couple of years ago,"},{"time":780000,"text":"a big program called the Foresight program --"},{"time":783000,"text":"lots and lots of people -- involved lots of experts --"},{"time":785000,"text":"everything evidence based -- a huge tome."},{"time":788000,"text":"But a piece of work we did was on: what five positive actions can you do"},{"time":791000,"text":"to improve well-being in your life?"},{"time":793000,"text":"And the point of these is"},{"time":795000,"text":"they are, not quite, the secrets of happiness,"},{"time":797000,"text":"but they are things that I think happiness will flow out the side from."}]},{"cues":[{"time":800000,"text":"And the first of these is to connect,"},{"time":803000,"text":"is that your social relationships"},{"time":805000,"text":"are the most important cornerstones of your life."},{"time":808000,"text":"Do you invest the time with your loved ones"},{"time":810000,"text":"that you could do, and energy?"},{"time":812000,"text":"Keep building them."},{"time":814000,"text":"The second one is be active."},{"time":816000,"text":"The fastest way out of a bad mood:"},{"time":819000,"text":"step outside, go for a walk, turn the radio on and dance."},{"time":822000,"text":"Being active is great for our positive mood."},{"time":825000,"text":"The third one is take notice."},{"time":828000,"text":"How aware are you of things going on around the world,"},{"time":831000,"text":"the seasons changing, people around you?"},{"time":834000,"text":"Do you notice what's bubbling up for you and trying to emerge?"},{"time":837000,"text":"Based on a lot of evidence for mindfulness,"},{"time":839000,"text":"cognitive behavioral therapy,"},{"time":841000,"text":"[very] strong for our well being."},{"time":844000,"text":"The fourth is keep learning"},{"time":846000,"text":"and keep is important --"},{"time":848000,"text":"learning throughout the whole life course."},{"time":850000,"text":"Older people who keep learning and are curious,"},{"time":853000,"text":"they have much better health outcomes than those who start to close down."},{"time":856000,"text":"But it doesn't have to be formal learning; it's not knowledge based."},{"time":858000,"text":"It's more curiosity."},{"time":860000,"text":"It can be learning to cook a new dish,"},{"time":863000,"text":"picking up an instrument you forgot as a child."},{"time":865000,"text":"Keep learning."},{"time":867000,"text":"And the final one"},{"time":869000,"text":"is that most anti-economic of activities,"},{"time":871000,"text":"but give."},{"time":873000,"text":"Our generosity, our altruism,"},{"time":875000,"text":"our compassion,"},{"time":877000,"text":"are all hardwired"},{"time":879000,"text":"to the reward mechanism in our brain."},{"time":881000,"text":"We feel good if we give."},{"time":883000,"text":"You can do an experiment where you give"},{"time":885000,"text":"two groups of people a hundred dollars in the morning."},{"time":888000,"text":"You tell one of them to spend it on themselves"},{"time":891000,"text":"and one on other people."},{"time":893000,"text":"You measure their happiness at the end of the day,"},{"time":895000,"text":"those that have gone and spent on other people are much happier"},{"time":897000,"text":"that those that spent it on themselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":900000,"text":"And these five ways,"},{"time":902000,"text":"which we put onto these handy postcards,"},{"time":905000,"text":"I would say, don't have to cost the earth."},{"time":908000,"text":"They don't have any carbon content."},{"time":910000,"text":"They don't need a lot of material goods to be satisfied."},{"time":914000,"text":"And so I think it's really quite feasible"},{"time":916000,"text":"that happiness does not cost the earth."},{"time":918000,"text":"Now, Martin Luther King,"},{"time":920000,"text":"on the eve of his death,"},{"time":922000,"text":"gave an incredible speech."},{"time":924000,"text":"He said, \"I know there are challenges ahead,"},{"time":927000,"text":"there may be trouble ahead,"},{"time":929000,"text":"but I fear no one. I don't care."},{"time":931000,"text":"I have been to the mountain top,"},{"time":934000,"text":"and I have seen the Promised Land.\""},{"time":936000,"text":"Now, he was a preacher,"},{"time":938000,"text":"but I believe the environmental movement"},{"time":940000,"text":"and, in fact, the business community, government,"},{"time":943000,"text":"needs to go to the top of the mountain top,"},{"time":946000,"text":"and it needs to look out,"},{"time":948000,"text":"and it needs to see the Promised Land,"},{"time":950000,"text":"or the land of promise,"},{"time":952000,"text":"and it needs to have a vision"},{"time":954000,"text":"of a world that we all want."},{"time":957000,"text":"And not only that, we need to create a Great Transition"},{"time":959000,"text":"to get there,"},{"time":961000,"text":"and we need to pave that great transition with good things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":964000,"text":"Human beings want to be happy."},{"time":967000,"text":"Pave them with the five ways."},{"time":969000,"text":"And we need to have signposts"},{"time":971000,"text":"gathering people together and pointing them --"},{"time":973000,"text":"something like the Happy Planet Index."},{"time":975000,"text":"And then I believe"},{"time":977000,"text":"that we can all create a world we all want,"},{"time":979000,"text":"where happiness does not cost the earth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":982000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}